PRIVACY NOTICE

This privacy notice describes how we might use your information if you download and use Chrome extension — Verified Bird.
Thank you for using Radosław Gryta's ("our", "we", "ourselves", "us") product.

1. WHAT INFORMATION DO WE COLLECT FOR OURSELVES?
None.

2. WHAT INFORMATION AND WHERE IS IT BEING STORED?
Extension settings (set by user and non-personal) are stored in Chrome in its "sync" module - meaning that these settings will remain even if you switch your machine as long as you (Chrome user) are logged into the browser.

3. HOW DO WE USE YOUR INFORMATION?
We do not use your information. Extension is using the settings information to keep the same settings between the sessions and machines.

4. WHAT ARE YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS?
You can write to us to delete information about you. But we won't do anything, because we won't have any information about or from you.

5. HOW CAN I MAKE SURE YOU'RE SAYING THE TRUTH?
If you don't trust this extension from Chrome Web Store, then feel free to install it on your own directly through github (after checking the source code to make sure you think it's safe). Instructions are included. Link to GitHub page: https://github.com/rgryta/Verified-Bird/

6. HOW CAN YOU CONTACT US ABOUT THIS NOTICE?     

If you have questions or comments about this notice, you may email us at radek.gryta+cws@gmail.com or by form attached within the store to:

Radosław Gryta
